
&nbsp;Bill of Personal Data Protection;
The Political Constitution of the Plurinational State of Bolivia, in Article NÂº130.

Any individual or collective person who believes to be unduly or illegally prevented from knowing, objecting or obtaining the deletion or rectification of the data registered by any physical, electronic means, magnetic or computer, in public or private files or databases, or that affect their fundamental right to personal or family privacy, or in their own image, honor and reputation, may file a Private Protection Action.Last modified 24 Jan 2022
				
			